# Mission {#mission}

venn is a social media application with the goal of making a way to forge connections by meeting people that are easy to bond with over common passions. Whether it is training cards or sports or politics, you should be able to find people that are able to match your vibes. 

# Database Design {#database-design}

This is a step by step construction of the database side of the project. What are the entities in this system? The attributes of those entities? The relationship between those entities?

## Components {#components}

These are entities, attributes and relationships of this system.

### Users {#users}

This is the information about accounts of users.

#### Attributes {#attributes}

id  
Username-(A name for your account)  
First Name  
Middle Name  
Last Name  
Preferred Name  
Town  
State  
Country

#### Relationships {#relationships}

User’s Passions (Users to Passions)  
Blocked Users (Users to Users)  
Friends (Users to Users)  
Followed Passions (Users to Passions)

### Passions {#passions}

The things users love to do and care about.

#### Attributes {#attributes-1}

id  
Title  
Description

#### Relationships {#relationships-1}

User’s Passions (Users to Passions)  
Related Passions (Passions to Passions)  
Subpassions (Passions to Passions)

### Posts {#posts}

#### Attributes {#attributes-2}

id  
Title  
Body  
Time Posted  
Group-(Posts can be posted in groups of posters) 

#### Relationships {#relationships-2}

Author (User to Post)  
Comments (Comment to Post)

### Groups {#groups}

#### Attributes {#attributes-3}

id  
Name  
Description

#### Relationships {#relationships-3}

Members (User to Group)  
Administrators (User to Group)  
Posts (Post to Group)  
Passions (Passion to group)

### Comments {#comments}

#### Attributes {#attributes-4}

id  
Author  
Body  
Time Posted  
Post

#### Relationships {#relationships-4}

Author (Comment to User)  
CommentedOnPost (Comment to Post)
